        <h2>
            Homemade Protein Bars
        </h2>
        <p> Beat your cravings with these delicious Homemade Protein Bars! </p>
        <p>
            Makes 5 Bars
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
            <li> 8 scoops chocolate protein powder</li>
            <li> 1 cup oatmeal</li>
            <li> 1/3 cup natural peanut butter</li>
            <li> 3 tbsp honey</li>
            <li> 1/2 cup 1% milk</li>
            <li> 3 tbsp crushed peanuts</li>
        </ul>
        </p>

        <p>
        <h3>Directions </h3>
        <ol>
            <li> Mix together the protein powder, oatmeal, peanut butter, honey and milk.</li>
            <li> Form into 5 bars and then roll in the crushed peanuts to finish.</li>
            <li> Place in the fridge for about 30-45 mins or until solid</li>
        </ol>
        </p>

        <p>
        <h3>Nutritional Facts</h3>
        <ol>
            <li> (Per Serving - 1 Bar) </li>
            <li> Calories: 452 </li>
            <li> Protein: 50g </li>
            <li> Carbohydrates: 36g </li>
            <li> Fat: 12g </li>
        </ol>
        </p>


